  "body": " Subspace topology  Let be a topological space and let be a subset. The subspace topology on has open sets of the form where is open. This is a very powerful construction that allows us to induce topologies on all manner of things. For instance, open intervals receive a topology in this way, as do open balls and the unit sphere If we do not specify otherwise, a subset of a topological space will always be endowed with the subspace topology.  "
